Backend Server (Node.js with Express.js):
server.js: Entry point of your server.
routes/: Directory to store route handlers.
userRoutes.js: Routes related to user authentication, profile management, etc.
postRoutes.js: Routes related to creating, updating, and fetching posts.
commentRoutes.js:Routes for adding comments to posts.
Other route files as per your app's features.
controllers/:Directory to store controller functions for each route.
